ttps%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fsouth-asia%2Fat-least-72-arrested-across-bangladesh-after-anti-israel-protests-turn-violent%2Famp_articleshow%2F120116519.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Is%20The%20Iran-US%20War%20Talk%20Ready%20To%20Be%20Retired%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIf%20there%20is%20one%20quality%20about%20the%20contours%20of%20Iran-US%20relations%20that%20isn't%20likely%20to%20change%20in%20the%20short%20run%2C%20it%20is%20its%20draining%20nature.%20When%20the%20inauspicious%20matchup%20between%20Mahmoud%20Ahmadinejad%20as%20Iran's%20president%20and%20George%20W.%20Bush%20in%20the%20White%20House%20escalated%20hostilities%20to%20all-time%20highs%20in%20the%202000s%2C%20many%20observers%20were%20convinced%20that%20nothing%20more%20menacing%20would%20be%20forthcoming.%20As%20the%20drumbeats%20of%20war%20can%20be%20heard%20anew%2C%20it%20is%20with%20the%20hindsight%20of%20history%20that%20we%20recognise%20the%20bleak%20status%20quo%20isn't%20unprecedented.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Bush%20added%20Iran%20to%20a%20hypothetical%20Axis%20of%20Evil%2C%20speculations%20about%20an%20inevitable%20war%20were%20omnipresent.%20Iran's%20leaders%2C%20in%20much%20less%20polished%20ways%20than%20today%2C%20challenged%20the%20US%20military%20might%2C%20brandishing%20their%20supposedly%20unbeatable%20resolve.%20On%20April%2029%2C%202010%2C%20in%20a%20public%20event%20at%20Kish%20Island%2C%20Ahmadinejad%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Cany%20hand%20that%20is%20raised%20from%20any%20corner%20of%20the%20world%20to%20pull%20the%20trigger%20against%20the%20people%20of%20Iran%20will%20be%20cut%20off%20from%20the%20arm%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMilitary%20Adventure%20Isn't%20Last%20Resort%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Washington%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20military%20adventure%20against%20Tehran%20has%20not%20ever%20been%20treated%20as%20an%20option%20of%20last%20resort.%20At%20least%20in%20the%20Republican%20Party%2C%20advocacy%20for%20war%20on%20Iran%20has%20remained%20an%20uncontroversial%2C%20if%20not%20mainstream%20position%2C%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20groups%20like%20Code%20Pink%20that%20have%20opposed%20it%20on%20humanitarian%20grounds%20have%20been%20portrayed%20as%20fringe%20and%20excessively%20progressive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202008%2C%20Pat%20Buchanan%2C%20the%20former%20communications%20director%20at%20the%20White%20House%20under%20President%20Ronald%20Reagan%2C%20suggested%20that%20Gen.%20David%20Petraeus%20had%20hinted%20at%20a%20military%20strike%20against%20Iran%20before%20the%20end%20of%20Bush's%20term.%20Buchanan%20had%20interpreted%20the%20former%20Commander%20of%20the%20United%20States%20Central%20Command's%20testimony%20before%20the%20Congress%20in%20April%20of%20that%20year%20to%20imply%20that%20a%20war%20plan%20was%20in%20the%20making.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELong%20before%20that%2C%20similar%20voices%20could%20be%20heard%2C%20prophesying%20a%20Tehran-Washington%20showdown%2C%20dragging%20the%20region%20into%20an%20extended%20period%20of%20chaos.%20Fortune-telling%20about%20the%20bombing%20of%20Iran's%20nuclear%20and%20military%20sites%20%E2%80%9Cby%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%E2%80%9D%20had%20become%20tedious%20in%20its%20repetitiveness.%20But%20it%20never%20ceased%20to%20be%20alarming.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20British%20MP%20and%20president%20of%20the%20Stop%20the%20War%20Coalition%2C%20Tony%20Benn%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20piece%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20build-up%20to%20a%20new%20war%20is%20taking%20exactly%20the%20same%20form%20as%20it%20did%20in%202002%E2%80%9D%2C%20drawing%20an%20analogy%20with%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20invasion%20of%20Iraq.%20The%20Iraq%20war%20was%20a%20massive%20operation%20that%20unseated%20one%20of%20the%20worst%20dictators%20of%20the%20region%2C%20and%20it%20came%20at%20a%20staggering%20humanitarian%20cost%2C%20unendorsed%20by%20the%20Security%20Council.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFirst%20we%20are%20being%20told%20that%20Iran%20poses%20a%20military%20threat%2C%20because%20it%20may%20be%20developing%20nuclear%20weapons%2C%E2%80%9D%20Benn%20wrote%2C%20lamenting%20that%20the%20British%20people%20could%20be%20persuaded%20into%20believing%20that%20supporting%20Bush's%20effort%20was%20the%20right%20thing%20to%20do.%20The%20proposed%20offensive%20was%20gaining%20momentum%20as%20it%20promised%20to%20avert%20a%20further%20crisis%20instigated%20by%20a%20country%20racing%20toward%20weapons%20of%20mass%20destruction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Iraq%20Lesson%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20its%20outcome%2C%20the%20war%20on%20Iraq%20didn't%20go%20down%20in%20history%20as%20a%20success%20story.%20Former%20Polish%20President%20Aleksander%20Kwasniewski%20told%20me%20in%202015%20that%20he%20believed%20the%20Iraq%20war%20was%20an%20example%20of%20an%20%E2%80%9Cunfinished%20business%E2%80%9D%20due%20to%20its%20%E2%80%9Cill-prepared%20and%20ill-executed%20stabilisation%20mission%E2%80%9D.%20Iran%20is%20almost%20four%20times%20the%20size%20of%20Iraq%20in%20terms%20of%20area%20and%20twice%20the%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20Barack%20Obama%20took%20over%2C%20conversations%20were%20underway%20about%20military%20action%20anchored%20in%20real%20anxieties%20about%20Tehran's%20provocations%20and%20lack%20of%20restraint%20on%20behalf%20of%20Washington%3B%20till%20then%2C%20Iranians%20hadn't%20yet%20elected%20Hassan%20Rouhani%20as%20their%20new%20president.%20Citing%20the%20Cato%20Institute's%20commentator%20Leon%20Hadar%2C%20%3Cem%3ENieman%20Reports%3C%2Fem%3E%20wrote%20in%20August%202012%2C%20%E2%80%9CFor%20journalists%20to%20assume%20that%20neither%20the%20US%20nor%20Israel%20will%20attack%20Iran%20before%20the%20November%20election%20could%20constitute%20another%20failure%20of%20imagination.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EObscured%20Perceptions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWar%20talk%20around%20Iran%20has%20not%20only%20featured%20prominently%20in%20the%20US%20media%20reports%2C%20but%20it%20has%20also%20obscured%20the%20perceptions%20of%20the%20two%20peoples%20of%20each%20other.%20Just%20as%20any%20nation%20may%20intuitively%20hold%20grudges%20against%20an%20adversary%2C%20Americans%20have%20often%20been%20told%20that%20Iran%20is%20the%20band%20of%20the%20resented%2C%20bad%20guys.%20It's%20not%20uncommon%20for%20people%20to%20lose%20sympathy%20with%20a%20nation%20that%20they%20believe%20will%20be%20a%20prospective%20belligerent%20on%20the%20battleground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202001%2C%20when%20Iran's%20nuclear%20controversy%20first%20broke%20out%2C%202018%20was%20the%20only%20year%20when%2015%25%20of%20Americans%2C%20according%20to%20Gallup's%20annual%20Perceptions%20of%20Foreign%20Countries%20survey%2C%20said%20they%20had%20%E2%80%9Cmostly%20favourable%E2%80%9D%20views%20of%20Iran.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20polling%20period%2C%20spanning%20February%201989%20to%20February%202025%2C%20has%20been%20characterised%20by%20smaller%20favourability%20rates%2C%20excluding%202004%2C%20the%20final%20year%20of%20reformist%20Mohammad%20Khatami's%20presidency.%20With%20his%20retirement%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20unfavourable%E2%80%9D%20views%20of%20the%20country%2C%20at%2031%25%2C%20began%20to%20increase%20irreversibly%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20overarching%20dynamics%20resemble%20the%20vibe%20of%20the%20Bush-Ahmadinejad%20era.%20The%20two%20governments%20refuse%20to%20accommodate%20each%20other.%20Iran's%20nuclear%20brinkmanship%2C%20despite%20President%20Masoud%20Pezeshkian's%20reassurances%20of%20its%20civilian%20nature%2C%20is%20in%20full%20swing.%20Meanwhile%2C%20as%20Iranians%20wrestle%20with%20frequent%20power%20blackouts%2C%20they%20wonder%20when%20the%20promise%20of%20affordable%20nuclear%20electricity%20will%20be%20fulfilled%20if%20the%20price%20has%20been%20living%20under%20sanctions%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIran%20As%20Just%20A%20'Launch%20Pad'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20that%2C%20Iran's%20regional%20activities%20no%20longer%20come%20across%20as%20political%20maneuvering%20to%20expand%20its%20sphere%20of%20influence%20as%20a%20regional%20power.%20The%20clerical%20establishment%2C%20fuelled%20by%20the%20apocalyptic%20ambitions%20of%20the%20Revolutionary%20Guards%2C%20is%20seeking%20to%20sow%20chaos%20in%20the%20region%20to%20perpetuate%20its%20hegemony%20at%20any%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20evidenced%20by%20its%20disregard%20for%20what%20millions%20of%20Iranians%20cherish%20as%20their%20ancestral%20heritage%2C%20including%20the%20Nowruz%20festivities%2C%20or%20its%20lackadaisical%20approach%20to%20resolving%20the%20deepening%20economic%20crisis%20of%20a%20nation%20beset%20by%20a%20hyperinflation%20of%2075%25%2C%20the%20Islamic%20Republic%20leadership%20doesn't%20have%20a%20vision%20for%20Iran%20as%20a%20country.%20It%20uses%20Iran%20as%20a%20launching%20pad%20to%20%E2%80%9Cexport%20the%20revolution%E2%80%9D%20and%20establish%20its%20fancied%20theocratic%20civilisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20its%20part%2C%20the%20US%20administration%20today%20subscribes%20to%20a%20foreign%20policy%20mantra%20that%20is%20neither%20revisionist%20nor%20revolutionary%2C%20but%20unconventional%20and%20eccentric.%20If%20the%20idea%20of%20annexing%20Canada%20as%20the%2051st%20state%20can%20be%20floated%20as%20official%20policy%2C%20a%20diplomatic%20or%20military%20shakeup%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%20implicating%20Iran%20won't%20be%20inconceivable.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20has%20been%20a%20long%20time%20since%20an%20American%20president%20spoke%20so%20aggressively%20about%20wanting%20to%20annex%20new%20territory%2C%20from%20Gaza%20to%20Greenland%2C%20the%20Panama%20Canal%2C%20and%20even%20Canada%2C%E2%80%9D%20wrote%20Michael%20McFaul%2C%20the%20former%20US%20ambassador%20to%20Russia%20and%20Stanford%20University%20professor%2C%20in%20a%20recent%20piece.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump's%20Letter%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Iran%20dilemma%20is%20one%20that%20the%20US%20president%20is%20determined%20to%20resolve%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible.%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20gone%20out%20of%20his%20way%20to%20write%20a%20personal%20letter%20to%20Ayatollah%20Ali%20Khamenei%2C%20asking%20for%20a%20deal.%20His%20letter%20was%20delivered%20to%20Tehran%20by%20an%20Emirati%20diplomat%20on%20March%2012.%20Answering%20Trump's%20letter%2C%20Khamenei%20green-lighted%20indirect%20talks%2C%20now%20scheduled%20for%20Saturday%2C%20April%2012%2C%20in%20Oman.%20And%20shortly%20after%20giving%20a%20nod%20to%20renewed%20diplomacy%2C%20in%20his%20Eid%20prayer%20sermon%2C%20he%20threatened%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfirm%20retaliatory%20blow%E2%80%9D%20in%20response%20to%20any%20outside%20aggression.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20it%20depends%20on%20the%20calculations%20of%20the%20senior%20cleric%20to%20prevent%20a%20further%20spiral%20of%20chaos%20in%20an%20already%20boiling%20region.%20Trump%20has%20reportedly%20set%20a%20two-month%20deadline%20for%20the%20two%20sides%20to%20achieve%20an%20understanding%20before%20%E2%80%9Cbad%2C%20bad%20things%E2%80%9D%20happen%20to%20Iran.%20As%20likely%20as%20it%20is%20that%20the%20crisis%20can%20be%20averted%2C%20there%20is%20a%20chance%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbad%20things%E2%80%9D%20may%20follow%20a%20failed%20stab%20at%20diplomacy.%20If%20the%20US%20president%20is%20taken%20for%20his%20word%2C%20that%20he%20remains%20opposed%20to%20forever%20wars%2C%20then%20the%20responsibility%20to%20initiate%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbombing%20the%20likes%20of%20which%20they%20have%20never%20seen%20before%E2%80%9D%20would%20have%20to%20be%20delegated%20to%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20of%20the%20Iran-Israel%20proxy%20conflict%20today%20is%20much%20different%20from%20what%20it%20looked%20like%20before%20April%2013%2C%202024%2C%20when%20Iran%20launched%20direct%20attacks%20on%20Israeli%20territory%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20retaliation%20for%20the%20latter's%20bombing%20of%20the%20Iranian%20embassy%20in%20Damascus%2012%20days%20earlier.%20Iran%20and%20Israel%20fired%20at%20each%20other%20again%2C%20and%20the%20mutual%20restraint%20that%20had%20created%20a%20theoretical%20buffer%20zone%20between%20the%20two%20nemeses%20was%20dislodged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Witkoff-Araghchi%20Exchange%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Middle%20East%20envoy%2C%20Steve%20Witkoff%2C%20an%20established%20real%20estate%20entrepreneur%2C%20has%20a%20track%20record%20of%20brokering%20agreements%20that%20have%20at%20least%20partly%20worked.%20His%20messaging%20has%20also%20been%20one%20that%20the%20Islamic%20Republic%20hasn't%20found%20objectionable%20per%20se.%20On%20April%201%2C%20Witkoff%20publicly%20reacted%20to%20an%20extended%20X%20post%20by%20Iran's%20foreign%20minister%2C%20Abbas%20Araghchi%2C%20reviewing%20the%20key%20provisions%20of%20the%202015%20nuclear%20deal%2C%20known%20as%20the%20Joint%20Comprehensive%20Plan%20of%20Action%20(JCPOA).%20Araghchi%20had%20written%20that%20the%20US%20president%20may%20not%20like%20the%20deal%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbut%20it%20contains%20one%20vital%20commitment%20by%20Iran%20which%20remains%20in%20place%2C%20and%20which%20even%20the%20US%20-%20being%20out%20of%20the%20deal%2C%20has%20benefited%20from%E2%80%9D.%20He%20then%20cited%20one%20passage%20from%20the%20159-page%20agreement%20that%20obligated%20Iran%20to%20never%20%E2%80%9Cseek%2C%20develop%20or%20acquire%20any%20nuclear%20weapons%E2%80%9D.%20Witkoff%20commented%20%26quot%3Bgreat%26quot%3B%20in%20response%20to%20Araghchi's%20post%2C%20a%20signal%20from%20the%20White%20House%20that%20could%20hardly%20be%20misunderstood.%20Under%20increasing%20criticism%2C%20however%2C%20he%20deleted%20his%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPredicting%20what%20happens%20next%20would%20be%20a%20fool's%20errand.%20Iranians%20reeling%20from%20foreign%20meddling%20and%20domestic%20authoritarianism%20are%20not%20a%20fan%20of%20their%20government's%20senseless%20rejections%20of%20overtures%20by%20successive%20US%20administrations.%20At%20this%20point%2C%20indirect%20talks%20may%20lead%20to%20a%20limited%20agreement%2C%20even%20though%20it's%20unlikely%20Trump%20would%20find%20a%20temporary%20agreement%20savoury%20enough%20to%20underwrite.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%20There%20Be%20A%20Fix%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20deal%20at%20all%20is%20no%20better%20than%20a%20limited%20deal%2C%20which%20anyway%20won't%20be%20an%20alternative%20to%20a%20lasting%20agreement.%20The%20Legatum%20Prosperity%20Index%20shows%20Iran%20is%20ranked%20126th%20out%20of%20167%20nations%20in%20different%20measures%20of%20governance.%20The%20Chandler%20Good%20Government%20Index%202024%20has%20assigned%20Iran%20a%20ranking%20of%20107%20out%20of%20113%20nations%20surveyed.%20The%20Islamic%20Republic's%20governance%20problem%20is%20not%20merely%20about%20its%20inability%20to%20address%20its%20foreign%20policy%20challenges%20through%20dialogue.%20It's%20more%20chronic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20form%20of%20Tehran-Washington%20contact%20at%20this%20fraught%20time%20will%20be%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20global%20stability.%20It%20promises%20betterment%20for%20the%20drained%20Iranians%20and%20preempts%20the%20elusive%20prospect%20of%20improved%20relations%20between%20Iran%20and%20the%20United%20States%20as%20former%20allies%20with%20deep%20cultural%20ties.%20It%20is%20not%20wishful%20thinking%20but%20constructive%20optimism%20to%20expect%20the%20two%20capitals%20to%20demonstrate%20the%20prudence%20that%20can%20spare%20the%20world%20the%20spectre%20of%20another%20conflict%20while%20the%20flames%20of%20those%20already%20raging%20haven't%20been%20extinguished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Kourosh%20Ziabari%20is%20a%20journalist%20and%20researcher%20of%20media%20studies.%20His%20writings%20have%20appeared%20in%20Foreign%20Policy%2C%20New%20Lines%20Magazine%2C%20and%20The%20American%20Conservative%2C%20among%20